      },
      "date": "2012-09-10 06:51:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nBob, mo_nomtab also controls osd lable. It seems that server still wants to update disk lable even if /etc/mtab is a symlink. If we set mo_nomtab before update_mtab_entry(), we lose information if user wants to update disk label. I'm not sure if it will cause any problems though.",
